{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["64-3JN-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"3JN"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["3 Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Yuhanna’s Third Letter \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["3 Yuhanna \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["3Jn \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Yuhanna’s Third Letter \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"3JN 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"3JN 1:1"},"The elder to Gaius the beloved, whom I love in truth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"3JN 1:2"},"Beloved, I pray that you may prosper in all things and be healthy, even as your soul prospers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"3JN 1:3"},"For I rejoiced greatly when brothers came and testified about your truth, even as you walk in truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"3JN 1:4"},"I have no greater joy than this: to hear about my children walking in truth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"3JN 1:5"},"Beloved, you do a faithful work in whatever you accomplish for those who are brothers and strangers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"3JN 1:6"},"They have testified about your love before the assembly. You will do well to send them forward on their journey in a way\nworthy of Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"3JN 1:7"},"because for the sake of the Name they went out, taking nothing from the Gentiles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"3JN 1:8"},"We therefore ought to receive such, that we may be fellow workers for the truth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"3JN 1:9"},"I wrote to the assembly, but Diotrephes, who loves to be first amongst them, doesn’t accept what we say.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"3JN 1:10"},"Therefore if I come, I will call attention to his deeds which he does, unjustly accusing us with wicked words. Not\ncontent with this, neither does he himself receive the brothers, and those who would, he forbids and throws out of the\nassembly. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"3JN 1:11"},"Beloved, don’t imitate that which is evil, but that which is good. He who does good is of Allah. He who does evil hasn’t\nseen Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"3JN 1:12"},"Demetrius has the testimony of all, and of the truth itself; yes, we also testify, and you know that our testimony is\ntrue. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"3JN 1:13"},"I had many things to write to you, but I am unwilling to write to you with ink and pen;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"3JN 1:14"},"but I hope to see you soon. Then we will speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by\nname. "]}]}